Kitutu Chache South MP Richard Onyonka has asked Kisii Governor James Ongwae not to support any NASA MP candidate. &ldquo;Leave us to battle it out alone, but I want assure you that we are behind you in your bid to retain the seat,&rdquo; he said.Onyonka spoke on Thursday during Ongwae&rsquo;s campaign in Sombogo, Kitutu Chache North constituency.Present were Deputy Governor Joash Maangi, ODM senator candidate Sam Ongeri, nominated Senator Janet Ong&rsquo;era, who is running for woman rep seat and ODM candidate Migosi Ogamaba, among others.Onyonka warned Ongwae he will be committing political suicide if he shows preference to any particular candidate. Ongwae told Onyonka he will heed his warning.&ldquo;I have keenly listened to what you said, Onyonka, and I will not go against the same. &ldquo;We must play a friendly fire game,&rdquo; he said. Ongwae said his opponents have nothing to offer and urged residents to examine their track records.He is facing a fierce battle from Senator Chris Obure of Jubilee, South Mugirango MP Manson Nyamweya of KNC and Lumumba Nyaberi of Wiper. disserviceOngeri said he defected from Jubilee to ODM because he realised Kenyans were unhappy with President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s administration because of his failure to provide services.He said Uhuru has failed to combat corruption, allowing a few individuals to steal from the public coffers.Ong&rsquo;era said she wants to help solve the problems of people living with disability, women and youth. Onyonka urged residents to give Ongwae a second opportunity to finish the projects he started.He drummed up support for NASA presidential flagbearer Raila Odinga.Jubilee has done a disservice to Kenyans for the nearly five years it has been in office, Onyonka said.